Think this is still company-wide? At least for many white collar work =
forces that will be remote for the next 6 to 12 months and from then on =
are likely to combine remote and office differently from before.

Basically we are saying to companies:

*	You have just made a large number of your teams virtual
*	Without any training in how to work virtually, or much experience
*	So these teams need behavioural help now, and behavioural help that =
keeps them aligned with your culture whilst they are remote
*	This will also help in the future of work that will be more focussed =
on remote=E2=80=A6=E2=80=A6

C

